sland's status since the seventeenth century. In recent years, the PRC has become dependent on international maritime commerce and has undertaken to expand considerably its navy to ensure access to the sea. PRC analysts concerned about strategy have articulated rationales for eliminating rival influences over Taiwan, the location of which is deemed as critical to China's projection of naval power. This book traces the evolution, explains the appeal, and suggests implications of the geostrategic calculations that pervade PRC strategic considerations of Taiwan.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Arms Control.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362637940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503626379423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503626379/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles